### What are you trying to do?

For years, it was advised not to make a shared material module (a module containing all the modules Angular Material offers), and rather import all components required in each module. 

This was advised because otherwise the size of the final bundle would be humongus. 

But out of curiosity, I have tested it yesterday, and it seems that now, the issue does not exist anymore : adding a shared material module changes the size of a pristine app by  whooping ... 7kB (out of 100kB). I would assume this is thanks to Ivy ? 

### What troubleshooting steps have you tried?

I tried building a pristine app with angular material by importing a single module (button module) : main is 99.35kB. 

I then added ALL modules into a shared module that I imported into my app module : main is 106.63kB. 

